00:32:40.259 --> 00:32:46.419
&gt;&gt;Male #1: Thank you for being here. My question
has to do with sales channel conflict. I'm

00:32:46.419 --> 00:32:53.249
quite curious as a discount seller of big
fashion clothing, you mentioned Ralph Lauren.

00:32:53.249 --> 00:32:57.780
What were the steps that you had to take and
the trials that you had to overcome in getting

00:32:57.780 --> 00:33:03.169
big brands to sign up without conflicting
with their existing sales channels?

00:33:03.169 --> 00:33:08.100
&gt;&gt;Alexis: It's not something that, well, first
of all of morphs to give in each area. So

00:33:08.100 --> 00:33:12.789
when you talk about sporting-goods it's very
different than fashion. And all of it we have

00:33:12.789 --> 00:33:18.590
to be mindful of now given how many categories
we're in as a business. But in the early days,

00:33:18.590 --> 00:33:26.210
first year, we would always come up against
pushback from department stores saying, you

00:33:26.210 --> 00:33:32.210
know, if you start working with these guys.
So we faced a lot of channel conflict there.

00:33:32.210 --> 00:33:38.830
And a couple of things, basically our end
brand partners needed us. They needed us because

00:33:38.830 --> 00:33:44.190
of the returns that they get back from department
stores. Any number of things that just weren't

00:33:44.190 --> 00:33:48.230
functioning well in their own distribution
channels out to market.

00:33:48.230 --> 00:33:55.110
But the second thing that's much more important
today in terms of every brand we work with,

00:33:55.110 --> 00:33:58.470
and something that we had to pivot our original
idea around. We really thought we just be

00:33:58.470 --> 00:34:05.970
a liquidator initially of desirable, desirable
product that given the seasonal construct

00:34:05.970 --> 00:34:10.600
of fashion they're already about to sell fall.
And are we thinking about buying fall woolen

00:34:10.600 --> 00:34:14.210
products right now? No, were thinking about
buying summer but that's a season old and

00:34:14.210 --> 00:34:18.140
that's what we're selling. We thought that
would be our business opportunity is just

00:34:18.140 --> 00:34:22.860
as messed up seasonal cycle in fashion and
being able to help brand partners with end

00:34:22.860 --> 00:34:27.850
of season goods.
But it more quickly, to our partners, really

00:34:27.850 --> 00:34:32.370
wanted to work with us because the context
their business was changing. Those that were

00:34:32.370 --> 00:34:37.570
coming into the stores were, tended to be
50 years old or older. They're having a really

00:34:37.570 --> 00:34:43.270
tough time reaching younger consumers who
are increasingly behind flat-panel monitors

00:34:43.270 --> 00:34:48.530
for 80 hours a week and not spending time
in stores. And they saw Gilt as a really unique

00:34:48.530 --> 00:34:57.230
way to reintroduce their brand, to acquire
customers, to even just reposition their brand

00:34:57.230 --> 00:35:00.700
in a number of different ways to an audience
that they were reaching otherwise.

00:35:00.700 --> 00:35:05.620
And that was our magic. That was why they
wanted to work with us. And it's still the

00:35:05.620 --> 00:35:10.940
case today. So they view us as a marketing
partner, marketing channel and customers often

00:35:10.940 --> 00:35:15.700
come to us for that sense of discovery of
a known brand, but being able to buy from

00:35:15.700 --> 00:35:22.400
it. And being able to discover something new
that they hadn't thought to buy before. And

00:35:22.400 --> 00:35:26.640
that's how we get over today is the fact that
we are equally a channel to reach a certain

00:35:26.640 --> 00:35:32.450
customer in a new way as a department store
is or even other channels like their own website

00:35:32.450 --> 00:35:35.750
might be for them is the business.
&gt;&gt;Sandra: Next question.

00:35:35.750 --> 00:35:41.950
&gt;&gt; Female #1: Hi, thank you so much for being
